refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
stringcubrid_get_server_info intlink_identifier
This function returns a string that represents the CUBRID server version.

 &reftitle.parameters;


  
    
  link_identifier

The CUBRID connection. If the link identifier is not specified, the last link opened by cubrid_connect is assumed.

  &reftitle.returnvalues;


   A string that represents the CUBRID server version; on success.
  


    &false; on failure.

  &reftitle.examples;
  
   cubrid_get_server_info example
   

<?php
    $link = cubrid_connect("localhost", 30000, "demodb2", "dba", "");
    if (!$link)
    {
        die('Could not connect.');
    }

    printf("CUBRID server info: %s\n", cubrid_get_server_info($link));
?>

   
    &example.outputs;
    

Result:
CUBRID server info: 8.2.1.0209
